                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d67">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Townsend</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Townsend reports that the Belgian Government is prepared to accept the
                    proposition of the Government of the United States, with the understanding that
                    “administrative entity” does not include Manchuria. The Belgian representatives
                    at St. Petersburg, Tokyo, and Peking will be instructed to that effect.)</p>
            </div>
